| Rebind at draw | Falsified — offset correct, still spikes |
| Read-past / `NumVertices` | Falsified — 400-primitive index probe clean |
| Deferred-write closes the gap | Falsified this run |
| “Per-draw drain doesn’t help” (CONSULT-24) | **Superseded** — drain masks **sampled** draws; unsampled majority still corrupt |

The hazard characterization in your prompt is the first one consistent with **all** measurements, including the discard inversion and the probe-selection asymmetry.

